    <note>Duan(1) Gu [21761] Renming Da cidian, p. 668, has an entry for Gu, who is not included in CBD. I am assuming that Gu was a descendant of Chengshi [21751], founder of the Jizhou, Yongxin county Duan(1), and that Weiyi(2) [21762] and Weixiu [21763] were sons--they may have been nephews, grandnephews or grandsons. I split the lineage with Zhun [21752], who moved to Jian county, making Gu and the Yongxin Duan(1), jia 'a' and Zhun and the Jian Duan(1), jia 'b.' Jiangxi TZ, 21.8a.</note>
